    </sectiondef>
    <sectiondef kind="user-defined">
      <header>PWM polarity flags</header>
      <description><para>The <computeroutput>PWM_POLARITY_*</computeroutput> flags are used with <ref refid="group__pwm__interface_1gaff280789f7b45fdefc354b3f841fe3ef" kindref="member">pwm_set_cycles()</ref>, <ref refid="group__pwm__interface_1gadd9049c9a56cd9419736b3514e42dc01" kindref="member">pwm_set()</ref> or <ref refid="group__pwm__interface_1ga9603146d7f9c2690c1e1983113d6c6bb" kindref="member">pwm_configure_capture()</ref> to specify the polarity of a PWM channel.</para>
<para>The flags are on the lower 8bits of the pwm_flags_t </para>
</description>
      <member refid="group__pwm__interface_1ga2c706bbada711f383d7b42f09dace861" kind="define"><name>PWM_POLARITY_NORMAL</name></member>
      <member refid="group__pwm__interface_1ga930c0ab50f81aeb571af9747947d7fae" kind="define"><name>PWM_POLARITY_INVERTED</name></member>
    </sectiondef>
